{"lemma":"شُفْعَةُ","slug":"شُفْعَةُ","root":"ش.ف.ع","root_slug":"ش-ف-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ف-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22635","n22639","n22640","n22641"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22635","headword_ar":"شَفَعَهُ","root":"$fE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoE","text_ar":"شَفْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, TA;) meaning (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a single thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawoj","text_ar":"زَوْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it to be one of a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it to be a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he adjoined it to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coupled it with, that which was a single thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~afoEu","text_ar":"الشَّفْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the adjoining"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna witorFA fa$afaEotuhu","text_ar":"كَانَ وِتْرًا فَشَفَعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witorFA fa$afaEotuhu biA=xara","text_ar":"وِتْرًا فَشَفَعْتُهُ بِا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was a single thing, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made it to be one of a pair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple, with another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh. [In Har p. 194, I find the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA=xr","text_ar":"با=خر"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAn wtrA f$f~Eh","text_ar":"كان وترا فشفّعه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. in like manner; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$f~Eh","text_ar":"شفّعه"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used I do not find in any lexicon: it may, however, be correctly thus used; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$f~E","text_ar":"تشفّع"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has the form, app. has also the signification, of its quasi-pass.]) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufiEa","text_ar":"شُفِعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almiloku bimilokK A=xara","text_ar":"المِلْكُ بِمِلْكٍ ا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"(here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was coupled by purchase with another possession:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufiEa bihi milokN","text_ar":"شُفِعَ بِهِ مِلْكٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had a possession coupled with it by purchase:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufoEapN","text_ar":"شُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEotu Alr~akoEapa","text_ar":"شَفَعْتُ الرَّكْعَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkEp","text_ar":"ركعة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA kaAna A^aboSaraniY bigir~aAti AlS~ibaY\n                      \n                     \n                        faA@loyawoma qado $ufiEato liYa A@loA^a$obaAHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How clear was my sight with the inadvertencies of youth! but to-day, objects have become doubled to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., I see the object [as] two objects, by reason of the weakness and dispersedness of my sight. (O, K. *) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says of a she-camel, (S, O,) and of a ewe, or she-goat, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEato","text_ar":"شَفَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She became such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiEN","text_ar":"شَافِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, O:) she is thus termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~a waladahaA $afaEahaA A^awo $afaEatohu","text_ar":"لِاَنَّ وَلَدَهَا شَفَعَهَا اَوْ شَفَعَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because her young one has made her to be one of a pair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with itself,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she has made it to be one of a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with another that is in her belly], (S, O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the inf. n. in this case is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ifoEN","text_ar":"شِفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr. (O, K.) ―         -b3-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laya$ofaEu EalaY~a biAlEadaAwapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيَشْفَعُ عَلَىَّ بِالعَدَاوَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY","text_ar":"لِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he aids"},{"kind":"text","text":"[another,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming"},{"kind":"text","text":"to him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of a pair, by enmity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against me, and acts injuriously to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conjointly"},{"kind":"text","text":"with another]. (O, K, TA.) Accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ofaEu","text_ar":"يَشْفَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He joins himself to another, and aids him, becoming to him one of a pair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afiyE","text_ar":"شَفِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an intercessor"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in doing good or evil, so that he aids him, or partakes with him, in [procuring] the benefit or the harm thereof; and thus it means in the saying in the Kur [iv. 87],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano ya$ofaEo $afaAEapF HasanapF","text_ar":"مَنْ يَشْفَعْ شَفَاعَةً حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and in what follows the same]: (TA:) or these words mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso adds a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deed to a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fAEp","text_ar":"شفاعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"here is a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instituting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prescribing, to another, a way of good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, so that he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imitates him, and thus becomes as though he were to him one of a pair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [But accord. to the expositors in general, and accord. to the general usage of the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as distinguished from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", what is here meant is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intercession."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa lahu","text_ar":"شَفَعَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"اـِلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K, * TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY AlA^amiyri","text_ar":"الى الاَمِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$f~E","text_ar":"تشفّع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$f~E","text_ar":"تشفّع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made petition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercession, for him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the prince"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus adjoining himself to him as an aider]: (MA, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa bayona Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"شَفَعَ بَيْنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He interceded between the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"], inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Jel in iv. 87:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEotu fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"شَفَعْتُ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [but the latter is scarcely to be found elsewhere thus used,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pleaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interceded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in favour of another,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for some means of access"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ingratiation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some right"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, * Msb, TA: *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned, but not explained, in the K: (TA:) as distinguished from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning as expl. above, it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joining oneself to another as an aider to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a petitioner respecting him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in most instances the former person is one of higher station than the latter: (Er-Rághib, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speaking of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afiyE","text_ar":"شَفِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercessor"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the king"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other person"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting some object of want which the speaker asks for another person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is also expl. as signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing over without punishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forgiving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"requesting, the passing over"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (for the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabu","text_ar":"طَلَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", probably accidentally omitted by the transcriber at the commencement of the explanation, should doubtless be supplied,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sins, crimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misdeeds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence, in a trad., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$ofaEo tu$af~aEo","text_ar":"اِشْفَعْ تُشَفَّعْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intercede thou: thou shalt have thine intercession accepted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) The saying in the Kur [ii. 117],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA tanofaEuhaA $afaAEapN","text_ar":"وَلَا تَنْفَعُهَا شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nor shall intercession profit it"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means that it shall have no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiE","text_ar":"شَافِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or intercessor] for his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEap","text_ar":"شَفَاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or intercession] to profit it; being a denial of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAfiE","text_ar":"شَافِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn- 'Arafeh, O, K;) and the same is the case in the Kur lxxiv. 49, (Ibn-'Arafeh, O, TA,) and xx. 108. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa","text_ar":"شَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaAEapN","text_ar":"شَفَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplicated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus Mbr and Th explain the words of the Kur [ii. 256],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano *aA A@l~a*iY ya$ofaEu Einodahu A_il~aA biA_i*onihi","text_ar":"مَنْ ذَا ا@لَّذِى يَشْفَعُ عِنْدَهُ اـِلَّا بِاـِذْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who is he that shall pray,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplicate, in his presence, except by his permission?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Accord. to El-Kutabee, (Mgh,) [i. e.] El-Kuteybee, (TA,) one says also, of a neighbour of one who desires to sell a dwelling [or land]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa A_ilayohi fiY maA baAEa","text_ar":"شَفَعَ اـِلَيْهِ فِى مَا بَاعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a demand to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. to the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting that which he sold"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the right of pre-emption"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and of the latter person, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fa$af~aEahu","text_ar":"فَشَفَّعَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and he admitted his right of pre-emption,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and he pronounced him to have a better right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"title,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"claim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a purchaser,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to that which was sold,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he whose connexion was more remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA. *)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa","text_ar":"شَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEN","text_ar":"شَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, tall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufiEa","text_ar":"شُفِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was smitten by the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA. [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufoEapN","text_ar":"شُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence.])"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","O","MA","IKtt"]},{"entry_id":"n22639","headword_ar":"شَفْعَةٌ","root":"$fE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in two places, near the end."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22640","headword_ar":"شُفْعَةٌ","root":"$fE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is used in relation to a house and to land; (S, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufuEapN","text_ar":"شُفُعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs, is a dial. var. thereof thus used. (TA.) It signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milok","text_ar":"مِلْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is coupled"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$ofuwE","text_ar":"مَشْفُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by purchase"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with one's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milok","text_ar":"مِلْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of land, previously possessed, and adjoining thereto"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh, Msb; *) from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna witorFA fa$afaEotuhu","text_ar":"كَانَ وِتْرًا فَشَفَعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above, in the second sentence of this art.]; (Mgh; [and the like is said in the Msb;]) a noun of the same class as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luqomapN","text_ar":"لُقْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolapN","text_ar":"فُعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb: *) this is the primary signification: then it was applied to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular kind of obtaining possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) [i. e.] it is also used as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obtaining possession of that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milok","text_ar":"مِلْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of land, by purchasing it, and coupling it with that previously possessed, and adjoining thereto"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) or one's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a demand respecting that which he seeks"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to possess, for the right of the pre-emption thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and adjoining it to that which he"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"already"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) and with the lawyers it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right of obtaining possession of a piece of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right of pre-emption thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against one's co-sharer whose possession is recent, by compulsion, for a compensation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right of obtaining possession of a piece of land, by compulsion, for"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the payment of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what it cost the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"former"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purchaser, by reason of partnership"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immediate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neighbourship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immediate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neighbourship with respect to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pre-emption of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS.) [See 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sqb","text_ar":"سقب"},{"kind":"text","text":".] El-Kutabee says, in explaining this word, in the Time of Ignorance, when a man desired to sell a house, his neighbour used to come to him and to make a demand to him ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa","text_ar":"شَفَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaba","text_ar":"طَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") respecting that which he sold [for the right of pre-emption], and he pronounced him to have a better right, or title, or claim, [as a purchaser,] to that which was sold, than he whose connexion was more remote: as though he took it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~afaAEapu","text_ar":"الشَّفَاعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the [right] derivation is that first mentioned. (Mgh.) We have not heard, (Mgh,) or there is not known, (Msb,) any verb belonging to it [in the classical language]. (Mgh, Msb.) Esh-Shaabee uses it in the first and in the second of the senses expl. above, [or nearly so,] in his saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano biyEato $ufoEatuhu wahuwa HaADirN falamo","text_ar":"مَنْ بِيعَتْ شُفْعَتُهُ وَهُوَ حَاضِرٌ فَلَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaTolubo *`lika falaA $ufoEapa lahu","text_ar":"يَطْلُبْ ذٰلِكَ فَلَا شُفْعَةَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He whose claimed possession to be coupled by purchase with one already belonging to him is sold when he is present without his demanding that"},{"kind":"text","text":"possession,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there shall be no obtaining possession for him by his purchasing it for that purpose"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh. [And the like is said in the Msb.]) Esh-Shaabee says [also],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ufoEapu EalaY ruw^uwsi AlrijaAli","text_ar":"الشُّفْعَةُ عَلَى رُوُوسِ الرِجَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The possession that is coupled by purchase with another possession is"},{"kind":"text","text":"apportioned"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the heads of the men"},{"kind":"text","text":"entitled thereto]: i. e., when the house is shared by a company of men whose shares are different, and one of them sells his portion, what is sold to his co-sharers is to be apportioned among them equally, according to their heads, not according to their [former] shares: (O, K, TA:) so in the Nh. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufoEapu AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"شُفْعَةُ الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two rek'ahs"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakoEataAni","text_ar":"رَكْعَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer that is performed in the period of the morning called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuHaY","text_ar":"ضُحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlDHY","text_ar":"الضحى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEapu","text_ar":"شَفْعَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) occurring in a trad., thus accord. to two different relations. (O.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diabolical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demoniacal, possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoEapN","text_ar":"شَفْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter expl. in this sense by IAar; and as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safoEapN","text_ar":"سَفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$unoEapN","text_ar":"شُنْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~apN","text_ar":"رَدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naZorapN","text_ar":"نَظْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [perceived] in the face: [see these words; the second and third of which generally mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unseemliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugliness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so, sometimes, does the last:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufoEapN","text_ar":"شُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here expl. on the authority of AA is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufaEN","text_ar":"شُفَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And IF states that it has been said to signify The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye, by which one is smitten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but he doubts its correctness; and thinks that it may be with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safoEapN","text_ar":"سَفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufoEapN","text_ar":"سُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["O","K","KT","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22641","headword_ar":"شُفُعَةٌ","root":"$fE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufoEapN","text_ar":"شُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}